Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.69,0:00:11.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.87,0:00:19.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Welcome back from the\Nother side of space-time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.41,0:00:21.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.21,0:00:24.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.37,0:00:29.30,Main,,0,0,0,,Will you teach me how to use\Nthis armillary compass of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.92,0:00:34.93,Main,,0,0,0,,I asked them, but they're awfully stubborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.30,0:00:39.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.01,0:00:40.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't tell him!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.35,0:00:41.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Pipe down!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.27,0:00:42.35,Main,,0,0,0,,What was that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.35,0:00:43.27,Main,,0,0,0,,You brat...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.27,0:00:46.10,Main,,0,0,0,,Stop it! Don't hurt them!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.10,0:00:47.86,Main,,0,0,0,,Certainly, I won't...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.86,0:00:50.65,Main,,0,0,0,,...if you do as I say.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.69,0:00:54.95,Main,,0,0,0,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.07,0:00:59.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.45,0:01:02.50,Main,,0,0,0,,You're a smart girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.96,0:01:09.04,Main,,0,0,0,,Mama... Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.51,0:02:40.05,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 11\NEdison's Resilience"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.05,0:02:41.51,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.\N"Episode 11\NEdison's Resilience"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.51,0:02:41.55,Main,,0,0,0,,"Episode 11\NEdison's Resilience"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.55,0:02:43.72,Main,,0,0,0,,By touching the portraits in the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.72,0:02:48.35,Main,,0,0,0,,the armillary compass\Ntakes you to that person's era.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.35,0:02:50.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.85,0:02:53.40,Main,,0,0,0,,You should have just made something up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.40,0:02:56.48,Main,,0,0,0,,You do run your mouth, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.53,0:02:59.57,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be a blabbermouth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:02.66,Main,,0,0,0,,than someone who ties\Npeople up and threatens them!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.53,0:03:06.16,Main,,0,0,0,,I finally see how he did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.16,0:03:10.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Why could he auction off\Nthe jade cup of Napoleon,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.50,0:03:14.29,Main,,0,0,0,,thought lost to the tides of history?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.29,0:03:17.30,Main,,0,0,0,,An invention that travels through time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:20.22,Main,,0,0,0,,This could mean big business.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.22,0:03:21.59,Main,,0,0,0,,Business?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:25.68,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.68,0:03:28.52,Main,,0,0,0,,An unparalleled travel experience\Nusing cutting edge technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:31.81,Main,,0,0,0,,...time travel.\NIf we label it that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.81,0:03:35.52,Main,,0,0,0,,we'll have people climbing over\Neach other for a chance to try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.52,0:03:36.77,Main,,0,0,0,,In addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.77,0:03:39.40,Main,,0,0,0,,things lost to war and natural disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.40,0:03:42.36,Main,,0,0,0,,like precious historical\Ndocuments, art, and sculptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.36,0:03:45.03,Main,,0,0,0,,If we could acquire them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.03,0:03:49.16,Main,,0,0,0,,they could fetch\Nincredible prices at auction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.45,0:03:53.25,Main,,0,0,0,,I won't let you abuse it like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:54.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Abuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.54,0:03:57.46,Main,,0,0,0,,What an awful thing to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.46,0:04:01.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Your husband is already doing that, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:05.97,Main,,0,0,0,,The jade cup of Napoleon\Nthat Mr. Mikage mentioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.97,0:04:08.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Someone brought it back from\Nthe past and sold it at an auction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:10.93,Main,,0,0,0,,It was likely Dr. Hayase.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.93,0:04:12.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.06,0:04:14.14,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase used the money from that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.14,0:04:19.69,Main,,0,0,0,,to pay back the money we had\Ninvested into his matter transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:21.65,Main,,0,0,0,,That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.65,0:04:23.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Just as your husband used it\Nto pay back our investment,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:27.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I will use this system for my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.74,0:04:30.08,Main,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.08,0:04:32.29,Main,,0,0,0,,When something is lost\Nin the course of history,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.29,0:04:36.75,Main,,0,0,0,,that means its role in history has ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.75,0:04:39.13,Main,,0,0,0,,To bring it back into the modern world
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.88,Main,,0,0,0,,is like twisting the very fabric of history!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.88,0:04:44.88,Main,,0,0,0,,The trifling sentimentality\Nof the historian...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:47.26,Main,,0,0,0,,It means little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.26,0:04:52.22,Main,,0,0,0,,What is needed in business\Nis the know-how to succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:03.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Isn't that... Dr. Hayase's...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.28,0:05:05.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.32,0:05:07.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, did something happen here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.91,0:05:11.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Oh, just a break-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.20,0:05:13.33,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? A break-in?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.33,0:05:16.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Come on, now. Go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.67,0:05:18.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Futa, let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.71,0:05:20.46,Main,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:28.30,Main,,0,0,0,,What era is Dr. Hayase in now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:30.47,Main,,0,0,0,,What will you do if we tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.47,0:05:34.14,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd like to have a long talk with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.14,0:05:37.27,Main,,0,0,0,,He broke our agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.27,0:05:40.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Broke your agreement? Papa did?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:44.07,Main,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hayase was developing\Na matter transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.07,0:05:47.70,Main,,0,0,0,,He had a duty to report\Nto us any phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.70,0:05:50.37,Main,,0,0,0,,that occurred during\Nthe course of that research.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.37,0:05:52.45,Main,,0,0,0,,But he didn't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.45,0:05:54.66,Main,,0,0,0,,If he returned the research funding,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:57.75,Main,,0,0,0,,doesn't that mean the contract is over?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.75,0:06:01.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sekota there used to be\Npart of Hayase's laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.96,0:06:06.34,Main,,0,0,0,,He was involved in the development\Nof the matter transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.34,0:06:10.97,Main,,0,0,0,,According to him, Dr. Hayase, during\Nthe development of the matter transporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.97,0:06:16.64,Main,,0,0,0,,through some accident, received a hint about\Nhow to use the system to travel through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:19.19,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, at the time\Nhe received that hint,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.19,0:06:22.23,Main,,0,0,0,,the contract was still in effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.23,0:06:24.78,Main,,0,0,0,,You sold out the secrets\Nof Hayase's research?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:27.44,Main,,0,0,0,,That's awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.44,0:06:31.74,Main,,0,0,0,,But the doctor is far more awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:36.04,Main,,0,0,0,,He deceived me, developed\Nthis incredible invention,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.04,0:06:37.91,Main,,0,0,0,,and hid it from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:42.33,Main,,0,0,0,,I must find him and receive recompense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.17,0:06:46.76,Main,,0,0,0,,All I want to do is talk to him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:49.01,Main,,0,0,0,,...in a businesslike manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.01,0:06:50.76,Main,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.76,0:06:55.01,Main,,0,0,0,,Of course, as compensation,\Nhe'll have to give this system to us,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:57.72,Main,,0,0,0,,and we'll have him help us with our business.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.44,0:07:01.44,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:04.19,Main,,0,0,0,,What era is Dr. Hayase in?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.48,0:07:10.28,Main,,0,0,0,,Then I'll just have to go looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.28,0:07:13.70,Main,,0,0,0,,But she'll be coming with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.70,0:07:18.50,Main,,0,0,0,,...to every era I visit,\Nuntil I find the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:21.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't do it! Don't drag Mari into this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.83,0:07:24.25,Main,,0,0,0,,It's Edison.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:32.34,Main,,0,0,0,,We lost track of Dr. Hayase\Nduring Edison's era.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.34,0:07:33.80,Main,,0,0,0,,Edison?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.94,0:07:46.19,Main,,0,0,0,,Edison, the master inventor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.19,0:07:50.07,Main,,0,0,0,,A great inventor and entrepreneur.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.07,0:07:52.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Then shall we head out, Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:53.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.49,0:07:54.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.36,0:07:57.28,Main,,0,0,0,,I told you where the doctor was!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:07:59.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Why are you taking Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.66,0:08:03.42,Main,,0,0,0,,You might do something\Nto make sure I can't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.42,0:08:07.84,Main,,0,0,0,,I want to make sure that you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:09.76,Main,,0,0,0,,We won't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:13.84,Main,,0,0,0,,In business, you always need\Ninsurance in case of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.84,0:08:17.47,Main,,0,0,0,,She is my insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.47,0:08:19.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Let go of Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:21.89,Main,,0,0,0,,And having your daughter with me
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:24.85,Main,,0,0,0,,will make negotiations with\Nthe doctor proceed more smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.85,0:08:26.15,Main,,0,0,0,,--You coward!\N--Stay where you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.15,0:08:28.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Well, here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:34.86,Main,,0,0,0,,--Mari!\N--Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.67,0:08:51.71,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1876\N(What is now) Menlo Park, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.71,0:08:55.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Are we really in Edison's time?\N"The Year 1876\N(What is now) Menlo Park, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:57.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Probably, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.89,0:09:03.93,Main,,0,0,0,,It seems it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.93,0:09:07.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Your father is an impressive man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.31,0:09:09.44,Main,,0,0,0,,What are you people doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:17.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Who are you people?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:20.66,Main,,0,0,0,,How'd you get in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:24.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Are you spies, come to steal my inventions?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:25.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Spies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.16,0:09:26.37,Main,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.37,0:09:30.59,Main,,0,0,0,,You've got a real scheming face on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.26,0:09:36.26,Main,,0,0,0,,He's got a good eye for people, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:39.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Your inventions...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.85,0:09:42.26,Main,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you're Mr. Edison?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.26,0:09:45.35,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right. I'm Edison.\NGot a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.35,0:09:47.02,Main,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.02,0:09:48.94,Main,,0,0,0,,So? What did you steal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.94,0:09:51.15,Main,,0,0,0,,We didn't steal anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.53,0:09:56.74,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.74,0:09:58.45,Main,,0,0,0,,Good to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:10:01.49,Main,,0,0,0,,Get going now. I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.49,0:10:05.25,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, well, er... I wanted\Nto ask you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:06.96,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.96,0:10:08.75,Main,,0,0,0,,We're looking for some--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.75,0:10:11.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Then look for them somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.71,0:10:15.34,Main,,0,0,0,,He's completely unapproachable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:17.05,Main,,0,0,0,,This is a ticker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.05,0:10:18.51,Main,,0,0,0,,Ticker?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.51,0:10:21.09,Main,,0,0,0,,It displays stock market quotes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.09,0:10:23.47,Main,,0,0,0,,During the speculation boom\Nfollowing the Civil War,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.47,0:10:28.23,Main,,0,0,0,,a trader's livelihood on Wall Street\Nrequired getting prices quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.23,0:10:30.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Before then, stock information
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.48,0:10:34.23,Main,,0,0,0,,was conveyed via\Ntelegraphs using Morse Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.23,0:10:39.99,Main,,0,0,0,,But he modified it to display\Nusing the alphabet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:43.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Thanks to him, transaction\Nspeeds increased rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:48.25,Main,,0,0,0,,It was the first of his inventions\Nthat made a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.25,0:10:49.92,Main,,0,0,0,,Money?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.92,0:10:53.79,Main,,0,0,0,,He was hoping to sell it for $5,000,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.79,0:10:56.67,Main,,0,0,0,,but it actually sold for $40,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:10:58.72,Main,,0,0,0,,For eight times the price?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.72,0:11:00.43,Main,,0,0,0,,That shows how much the buyer
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.43,0:11:04.85,Main,,0,0,0,,was able to foresee the value of the ticker.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.85,0:11:07.27,Main,,0,0,0,,You seem to know your stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:09.02,Main,,0,0,0,,This is an electric pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.02,0:11:13.11,Main,,0,0,0,,This is... most likely\Na prototype photocopier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:15.40,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.40,0:11:19.32,Main,,0,0,0,,You were my idol when I was a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.32,0:11:20.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.45,0:11:23.12,Main,,0,0,0,,How old are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.12,0:11:24.83,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm only 29!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.83,0:11:26.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.41,0:11:29.83,Main,,0,0,0,,There's some complicated\Ncircumstances surrounding this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:33.46,Main,,0,0,0,,--The truth is, we're from the future.\N--Now that I look closer,\Nyou have good, honest eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:38.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Um... Um... Are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:40.22,Main,,0,0,0,,I take it all back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.22,0:11:42.88,Main,,0,0,0,,He doesn't have a good eye for people at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.88,0:11:45.05,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Mikage...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:49.06,Main,,0,0,0,,He's honest when it comes to\Nbusiness-- the best there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.10,0:11:52.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Is this a telephone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.85,0:11:55.36,Main,,0,0,0,,I know this! It's Mr. Bell's!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.36,0:11:56.31,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.31,0:12:01.19,Main,,0,0,0,,I tried to make one based\Non the one Bell exhibited
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.19,0:12:03.28,Main,,0,0,0,,at the Centennial Exhibition in Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:04.53,Main,,0,0,0,,You made it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.53,0:12:05.57,Main,,0,0,0,,As I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.57,0:12:09.83,Main,,0,0,0,,It's really well-made. Bell's a smart guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.83,0:12:13.00,Main,,0,0,0,,As I recall, you were also\Nworking on a telephone,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.00,0:12:15.75,Main,,0,0,0,,but Bell beat you to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.75,0:12:18.34,Main,,0,0,0,,And patented it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:19.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:20.92,Main,,0,0,0,,It was frustrating, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:22.67,Main,,0,0,0,,What can you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.67,0:12:26.64,Main,,0,0,0,,But there's plenty of room\Nto improve the telephone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:30.10,Main,,0,0,0,,First, the transmitter and receiver\Nbeing one-way is inconvenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.10,0:12:32.93,Main,,0,0,0,,It's one-way?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:34.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Look at that carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:41.44,Main,,0,0,0,,You can send words through on that,\Nbut you can't receive them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.44,0:12:43.24,Main,,0,0,0,,Inconvenient, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.24,0:12:44.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.70,0:12:47.70,Main,,0,0,0,,So I'm working on a way
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.70,0:12:49.99,Main,,0,0,0,,that you can hear what they're\Nsaying while using the transmitter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.99,0:12:54.21,Main,,0,0,0,,I think it would be really\Nconvenient to have it be two-way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:55.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.71,0:12:58.29,Main,,0,0,0,,And Bell's telephone
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:02.67,Main,,0,0,0,,converts the vibrations of the voice into\Nelectric current with an electromagnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.67,0:13:05.51,Main,,0,0,0,,but it can only carry the voice\Nabout one kilometer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:07.72,Main,,0,0,0,,and the sound is muffled.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:12.18,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm developing a microphone that\Nwill make sound travel more clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:16.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Carbon granules seem like they're\Nbetter suited than the electromagnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.48,0:13:18.98,Main,,0,0,0,,but I'm still figuring out\Nwhere to go from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.98,0:13:22.44,Main,,0,0,0,,I've tried out over 500 versions,\Nbut it's not going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:24.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Five hundred?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.36,0:13:27.03,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm getting so sick of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.03,0:13:29.83,Main,,0,0,0,,But even if I fail 1,000 times,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.83,0:13:32.29,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll keep going until I succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:39.33,Main,,0,0,0,,This is... a phonograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:41.09,Main,,0,0,0,,That's a work in progress, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.09,0:13:43.80,Main,,0,0,0,,I thought it up while I was\Nworking on the telephone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.80,0:13:46.51,Main,,0,0,0,,If you can send a voice long-distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.51,0:13:50.35,Main,,0,0,0,,what if you could also store it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.47,0:13:55.68,Main,,0,0,0,,He's so dynamic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.68,0:13:58.69,Main,,0,0,0,,What do successful people have in common?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.69,0:14:02.19,Main,,0,0,0,,An indomitable will to fight,\Nforward-thinking ideas,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.19,0:14:05.28,Main,,0,0,0,,and unfounded self-confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.36,0:14:08.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Having just one isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.03,0:14:12.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Those who have them all succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.03,0:14:15.75,Main,,0,0,0,,I know why Edison was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.75,0:14:19.79,Main,,0,0,0,,To be honest, when Bell got the drop on me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.79,0:14:22.59,Main,,0,0,0,,I was so depressed, I nearly\Nlost my will to keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.59,0:14:24.21,Main,,0,0,0,,But I got some advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:26.46,Main,,0,0,0,,It was from an Easterner, like you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.46,0:14:27.80,Main,,0,0,0,,An Easterner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.80,0:14:28.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:31.22,Main,,0,0,0,,He said, "You've always bounced\Nback from your failures
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.22,0:14:36.56,Main,,0,0,0,,to keep trying new inventions."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:38.10,Main,,0,0,0,,That person...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.10,0:14:41.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Was his name Eiji Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.48,0:14:43.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Eiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.06,0:14:45.61,Main,,0,0,0,,Was that his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:48.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Anyway, his words made me remember
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.70,0:14:51.87,Main,,0,0,0,,that I was burning with the will to invent.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:54.16,Main,,0,0,0,,Where is that man now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.16,0:14:56.70,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh? He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.70,0:14:57.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.83,0:15:00.75,Main,,0,0,0,,He said something about\Nmeeting me again in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.75,0:15:03.54,Main,,0,0,0,,I didn't get it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:05.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Future?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.00,0:15:08.97,Main,,0,0,0,,He said I was going to\Nbring light to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:10.47,Main,,0,0,0,,Light?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.47,0:15:13.26,Main,,0,0,0,,He "wanted to be witness to\Nthat moment," or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:15.01,Main,,0,0,0,,What a weirdo--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.01,0:15:16.81,Main,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:18.77,Main,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.77,0:15:20.85,Main,,0,0,0,,--Hey!\N--Where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.85,0:15:24.02,Main,,0,0,0,,After Dr. Hayase, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:25.98,Main,,0,0,0,,And if I may offer some unsolicited advice...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.98,0:15:28.11,Main,,0,0,0,,...if you're going to come late\Nto an invention's development,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.11,0:15:30.36,Main,,0,0,0,,first, make your own company,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:32.32,Main,,0,0,0,,and solicit investors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.32,0:15:36.20,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't listen to what this bad guy says!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.20,0:15:38.12,Main,,0,0,0,,Bad... guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.12,0:15:41.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but when it comes to business,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.41,0:15:43.71,Main,,0,0,0,,I say nothing but beneficial things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.71,0:15:45.63,Main,,0,0,0,,Ow! That hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.63,0:15:48.46,Main,,0,0,0,,Don't pull me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.46,0:15:50.97,Main,,0,0,0,,My own company, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:55.64,Main,,0,0,0,,You wanted to go after Papa,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.64,0:15:58.72,Main,,0,0,0,,but we don't know how many\Nyears into the future he's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:00.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Untrue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.27,0:16:01.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.35,0:16:04.27,Main,,0,0,0,,He's visiting the day Edison\Nbrought light to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.27,0:16:06.69,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, the\Ninvention of the light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:10.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?! Mr. Edison invented the light bulb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.82,0:16:15.03,Main,,0,0,0,,Learn a little more history, would you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.03,0:16:17.99,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm doing the best I can!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:24.04,Main,,0,0,0,,In 1879, Edison completed\Nthe Edison light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:25.42,Main,,0,0,0,,Edison light bulb?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:28.71,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, on October 21st.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.71,0:16:32.76,Main,,0,0,0,,The success of it allowed for\Nthe first practical light bulbs,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.76,0:16:36.64,Main,,0,0,0,,and the technology was quickly\Nadopted across the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.64,0:16:39.85,Main,,0,0,0,,So, how do we travel to that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.85,0:16:41.02,Main,,0,0,0,,We can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.14,0:16:46.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten the position you're in?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.23,0:16:51.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hayase moves where he wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.82,0:16:53.74,Main,,0,0,0,,It can't be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.74,0:16:58.62,Main,,0,0,0,,I'll ask again: How do we\Ntravel to October 21st?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.79,0:17:02.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.75,0:17:05.04,Main,,0,0,0,,The Mizuki boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:07.67,Main,,0,0,0,,You've been watching us, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.67,0:17:08.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.84,0:17:10.38,Main,,0,0,0,,Send us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.38,0:17:14.51,Main,,0,0,0,,...to October 21st, 1879.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.30,0:17:18.43,Main,,0,0,0,,You hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.43,0:17:22.35,Main,,0,0,0,,You'd better not try any funny business.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.69,0:17:29.23,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:32.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Eiji has one of those armillary\Ncompasses too, doesn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:34.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Can't we get in contact with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.15,0:17:36.24,Main,,0,0,0,,According to my brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.24,0:17:39.95,Main,,0,0,0,,the armillary compass the doctor\Nhas is from three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.95,0:17:45.66,Main,,0,0,0,,so it's synced to the system from three\Nyears ago, and we can't communicate with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.66,0:17:47.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Quit whispering!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.50,0:17:49.79,Main,,0,0,0,,Settings complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.79,0:17:51.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:18:00.93,Main,,0,0,0,,"The Year 1879\N(What is now) Menlo Park, America"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:10.69,Main,,0,0,0,,Two minutes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.69,0:18:12.61,Main,,0,0,0,,That's the shortest one yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.61,0:18:16.03,Main,,0,0,0,,I know! You don't have to\Nreport every little thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.03,0:18:18.82,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Edison! It's been a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.82,0:18:20.53,Main,,0,0,0,,Do you remember us?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.53,0:18:23.87,Main,,0,0,0,,You two... Get down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.25,0:18:27.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Another one appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.75,0:18:30.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Are all Easterners magicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.88,0:18:32.50,Main,,0,0,0,,Easterners?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.50,0:18:34.21,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa's here, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.21,0:18:36.55,Main,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.55,0:18:39.01,Main,,0,0,0,,He came out of thin air, just like you did,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.01,0:18:41.89,Main,,0,0,0,,and he broke my light bulb,\Njust like you did!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.89,0:18:46.14,Main,,0,0,0,,After we'd just set a record\Nfor 35 continuous hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:47.64,Main,,0,0,0,,We're very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.64,0:18:49.56,Main,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go again!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:50.27,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.27,0:18:51.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.06,0:18:54.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Um, Mr. Edison...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.15,0:18:55.32,Main,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:56.90,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.90,0:18:59.15,Main,,0,0,0,,Where is Dr. Hayase?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.15,0:19:00.41,Main,,0,0,0,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:03.37,Main,,0,0,0,,The phonograph?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.37,0:19:05.87,Main,,0,0,0,,He told me to let his daughter\Nplay it when she showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.25,0:19:11.88,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari, I'll be waiting in\Nthe warehouse out back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:13.71,Main,,0,0,0,,That's Papa's voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.71,0:19:15.67,Main,,0,0,0,,Where's the warehouse out back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.67,0:19:17.76,Main,,0,0,0,,It's out back, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.76,0:19:18.80,Main,,0,0,0,,We're starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.97,0:19:23.05,Main,,0,0,0,,I'd like to witness this moment in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.05,0:19:25.39,Main,,0,0,0,,But I need to speak to Dr. Hayase first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.11,0:19:37.40,Main,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:41.61,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on? Those clouds\Nappeared so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:47.41,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! What did you do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.41,0:19:48.95,Main,,0,0,0,,I didn't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.95,0:19:50.37,Main,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.37,0:19:51.58,Main,,0,0,0,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.58,0:19:53.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Shun?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.00,0:19:54.79,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.42,0:19:58.17,Main,,0,0,0,,Hey! Wh-What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.17,0:19:59.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Stay right by my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.07,0:20:20.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari! Close your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.74,0:20:28.91,Main,,0,0,0,,Your reactions are surprisingly quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.91,0:20:30.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.08,0:20:31.37,Main,,0,0,0,,Hayase...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.75,0:20:34.92,Main,,0,0,0,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.83,0:20:39.84,Main,,0,0,0,,Edison told you I was with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.84,0:20:41.34,Main,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.34,0:20:45.68,Main,,0,0,0,,But why were you able\Nto time travel with Mari?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:49.64,Main,,0,0,0,,The armillary compass!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.64,0:20:50.93,Main,,0,0,0,,Why do you have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.93,0:20:54.48,Main,,0,0,0,,Waka found it in the\Nbasement of the laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.48,0:20:57.15,Main,,0,0,0,,It had fallen next to the machine, she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.15,0:21:02.24,Main,,0,0,0,,She said you'd probably\Nprepared it for her, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.24,0:21:04.78,Main,,0,0,0,,Could I have made it later?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.78,0:21:08.41,Main,,0,0,0,,But I've gotta tell you, Mom's super mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.41,0:21:09.87,Main,,0,0,0,,What? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.87,0:21:14.00,Main,,0,0,0,,This guy in the past... Napoleon?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:14.96,Main,,0,0,0,,That guy's cup?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.96,0:21:17.13,Main,,0,0,0,,Because you took it and sold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.13,0:21:18.67,Main,,0,0,0,,She found out?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.67,0:21:20.67,Main,,0,0,0,,That's so bad...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.67,0:21:24.34,Main,,0,0,0,,I'm too scared to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.34,0:21:26.09,Main,,0,0,0,,Papa...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.09,0:21:27.76,Main,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:32.14,Main,,0,0,0,,It's better for me that you don't go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.14,0:21:38.02,Main,,0,0,0,,Then we could have the time travel\Nsystem all to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.07,0:21:48.99,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.99,0:21:50.70,Main,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:55.54,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.54,0:21:56.66,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.83,0:22:00.84,Main,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.85,0:22:18.77,Main,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.77,0:22:20.69,Main,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.45,0:22:29.99,Main,,0,0,0,,"Next Episode: Cherished Scientists"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.08,0:24:00.66,Main,,0,0,0,,"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.66,0:24:03.00,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!\N"Mari and Waka's Quick Science"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.00,0:24:04.08,Main,,0,0,0,,Mari and Waka's Quick Science!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.08,0:24:06.96,Main,,0,0,0,,He's visiting the day Edison\Nbrought light to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.96,0:24:09.55,Main,,0,0,0,,In other words, the invention\Nof the light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.55,0:24:12.68,Main,,0,0,0,,Huh?! Mr. Edison invented the light bulb?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.22,0:24:17.26,Main,,0,0,0,,This is the light bulb Mr. Edison invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.26,0:24:20.06,Main,,0,0,0,,Before him, there had been issues\Nwith the resilience of the filament,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.06,0:24:23.35,Main,,0,0,0,,and light bulbs weren't practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.35,0:24:25.15,Main,,0,0,0,,What issues?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.15,0:24:29.36,Main,,0,0,0,,Filaments of the time were primarily\Nmade from processed charcoal,\N"Filament"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.36,0:24:32.99,Main,,0,0,0,,and they produced heat\Nand light at the same time.\N"Filament"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.99,0:24:33.82,Main,,0,0,0,,"Filament"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.41,0:24:40.75,Main,,0,0,0,,Let's experiment with mechanical pencil lead,\Nwhich is made from charcoal and carbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.75,0:24:42.79,Main,,0,0,0,,It's shining!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.79,0:24:44.83,Main,,0,0,0,,Actually, it's burning!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.92,0:24:49.46,Main,,0,0,0,,You can't use that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.46,0:24:54.47,Main,,0,0,0,,To make light bulbs practical, they had\Nto do something to prevent oxidation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.47,0:24:55.72,Main,,0,0,0,,Oxidation?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.72,0:24:59.35,Main,,0,0,0,,Oxygen is what makes things burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.35,0:25:03.85,Main,,0,0,0,,Is it possible... there's no\Noxygen inside light bulbs?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.85,0:25:08.90,Main,,0,0,0,,This time, we'll fill the vessel\Nwith helium to drive out the oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.90,0:25:11.82,Main,,0,0,0,,--It's not catching fire!\N--I was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.82,0:25:14.49,Main,,0,0,0,,But it's slowly melting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.49,0:25:17.87,Main,,0,0,0,,Even if it doesn't burn,\Nthe continuous heat put out
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.87,0:25:20.70,Main,,0,0,0,,causes the filament to weaken and snap.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.70,0:25:25.04,Main,,0,0,0,,He performed thousands of resilience\Ntests to make a practical light bulb.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.04,0:25:29.96,Main,,0,0,0,,Mr. Edison's resilience\Nbrought light to the world, huh?
